item.title: Charlie Kirk Is Dead After Utah Valley University Shooting
item.description: Turning Point USA cofounder Charlie Kirk was shot at an event at Utah Valley University on Wednesday. He later died from his injuries.

item.title: 3 Exciting Camera Features on Apple’s New iPhone 17 Lineup
item.description: An upgraded selfie camera with a square sensor, dual camera capture, and 8X optical-like image quality has me excited about the new iPhone 17 models.

item.title: Our Favorite Earbuds for Working Out Are Cheaper Than Ever
item.description: The Beats Powerbeats Pro 2 are $50 off on Amazon.

item.title: YouTube’s multi-language audio feature for dubbing videos rolls out to all creators
item.description: YouTube's multi-language audio feature is rolling out to millions of creators, helping them reach a wider global audience.

item.title: Klarna’s IPO pops, raising $1.4B, with Sequoia as the biggest winner
item.description: Of the 34.3 million shares Klarna sold, only 5 million were sold by the company, it said. The rest were sold by existing investors.

item.title: While US stalls, Australia and Anduril move to put XL undersea vehicle into service
